1. Scope and safety rules
Scope: Implement and extend the SA JKA National Dan Grading workflow only.
Critical constraint:
Do not modify any existing features or logic outside the National Gradings function.
Add new components, screens, and backend logic in separate modules/files. The existing system must remain as is.
This tells Copilot Agent explicitly to keep its hands off the rest of your platform.

2. Screen 1 – National Grading application (Sensei view)
Purpose: Sensei logs into their profile and completes the entire Dan grading application online for one student, with strict rule enforcement.

2.1 Student information (top card)
Fields at top of screen (always visible):
Date of grading – dropdown list of scheduled national grading dates.
Name – text.
Surname – text.
Date of birth – date picker.
Attempted Dan level – dropdown (1st Dan, 2nd Dan, 3rd Dan, 4th Dan, 5th Dan).
Dojo – dropdown of registered SA JKA dojos.
Cell number – text.
Email address – text with email validation.

Behaviour:
When Date of Birth + Attempted Dan level are captured:
Backend calculates age from Date of Birth and compares to Dan level requirements.

Age rules:
1st Dan: age ≥ 12
2nd Dan: age ≥ 14
3rd Dan: age ≥ 16
4th & 5th Dan: age ≥ 18

If age requirement is not met:
All subsequent sections stay greyed‑out/disabled.
Show a clear error message explaining which age rule failed.

If age requirement is met:
Unlock the next card (“Eligibility requirements”).

3. Eligibility requirements (middle cards)
This section is only enabled if age requirements are met.

3.1 Affiliation / training time rules
For the selected Attempted Dan level:

1st Dan – minimum 4 years paid affiliations in blue book.
2nd Dan – 2 years consecutive training from last grading date to current grading date (no short time allowed).
3rd Dan – 3 years consecutive training from last grading date to current grading date.
4th Dan – 4 years consecutive training from last grading date to current grading date.
5th Dan – 5 years consecutive training from last grading date to current grading date.

System logic:
Read last grading date and training/affiliation data from existing records.
Calculate exact years between last grading date and current grading date; must be ≥ required years for that Dan level.
If requirement not met → stop progression, show clear message, keep next cards locked.

3.2 Pre‑gradings and duties rules
Per Attempted Dan level:

1st Dan – 2 pre‑gradings and 1 table official duty.
2nd Dan – 2 pre‑gradings and 2 table official duties.
3rd Dan – 3 pre‑gradings and 2 judging duty and South African judging qualification.
4th Dan – 3 pre‑gradings and 2 judging duty and International D judging qualification.
5th Dan – 3 pre‑gradings and 2 judging duty and International D judging qualification.

System logic:
Read pre‑grading attendance records and official/judging duty/judging qualification logs from existing tables.
Validate that counts meet minimum requirements for the attempted Dan level.
If any count is missing/insufficient → block progression and show message.
Only when all affiliation, training, pre‑grading, and duty rules are satisfied → unlock the Indemnity card.

Global rule:
If any requirement (age, time, duties) is not met, the form must not proceed to indemnity or payment.

4. Indemnity and grading form
4.1 Indemnity form card
Once all requirements are valid:
Show full indemnity text on screen.

Display key student details at the top (name, surname, dojo, attempted Dan level, grading date).
Provide electronic signature and date fields (e.g. typed name + checkbox “I agree” + date).
Student (or Sensei on behalf) must sign and date electronically before proceeding.

4.2 Auto‑generated Dan Grading application form
After indemnity is signed:
Generate the Dan Grading form on screen, pre‑filled with all captured and validated data.
Show a “Print form” button.

When printed:
Set a flag formPrinted = true.
Show a visual indication on screen, e.g. “Form printed – please sign and submit to Sensei Brad Korras for Japan.”
The printed form is for physical signature and submission to Sensei Brad Korras.

5. Payment and automated email
5.1 Cart and payment
Add pre‑grading and grading fees into a cart for this application.
Allow online payment completion via the existing payment system (you will later specify gateway).

On successful payment:
Mark application as “Paid”.

5.2 Automated email
On successful payment:
Send email to brad@karate.co.za.
Subject: "[Name Surname] – [Attempted Dan Level]".
CC: student email address captured in the form.

Attach:
Indemnity form (PDF or generated document).
Grading application form.
Proof of payment generated by the system.

This makes Brad’s inbox the single source for completed, paid applications for Japan.

6. Gamified UI + colour scheme
Apply your gamified layout with Tailwind‑style classes:
Page background: bg-gray-50.
Cards: bg-white with border-gray-200 and rounded corners, treated like “levels” the user unlocks.
Primary maroon: color: hsl(355, 35%, 40%) for card headers, main title, and key branding.
Primary action buttons (e.g. “Next step”, “Proceed to indemnity”, “Pay now”): bg-orange-500 with appropriate hover state.
Text:
Headers: text-gray-900.
Secondary text/help: text-gray-600.
All form labels and inputs consistent with this colour scheme.
Secondary links (e.g. “View syllabus”, “Download previous grading history”): blue accent (e.g. text-blue-600).
Optional gamification examples: progress bar showing Step 1–4, badges for “All requirements met”, etc.

7. Export to Excel for Brad
Add a requirement for a Brad‑only export button:
Role: accessible to Sensei Brad (or admin panel for National Gradings).
Location: National Gradings admin screen (not student form).

Function:
Button label: e.g. “Export current grading applications to Excel”.
When clicked, export all current national grading applications for the upcoming grading date into an Excel file (.xlsx).
Columns include at least:
Grading date
Name
Surname
Date of birth
Age
Attempted Dan level
Dojo
Cell number
Email address
Affiliation/training years (numeric)
Pre‑gradings count
Table official / judging duties count
Indemnity signed (Yes/No, date)
Form printed (Yes/No, date)
Payment status (Paid/Unpaid)
Proof of payment reference/ID
Export behaviour:
Filter applications to the selected upcoming grading date so Brad sees only that event.
Generate and download the Excel file with one row per application
